# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Emberline — .gitignore
#
# Scope policy: only ignore files that are
#   - generated at runtime or setup time
#   - operational / ephemeral (logs, temp state)
#   - secrets or environment-specific
#   - deploy artifacts intentionally not published
#   - local editor / OS noise
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Node dependencies
node_modules/

# Assets fetched by setup-assets.js (run once after clone — never committed)
fonts/*.woff2
fonts/fonts.css
vendor/*.min.js

# Operational runtime logs — must never be committed
*.log

# Environment and secrets
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Deployment artifacts deliberately not part of the public repo.
# Canonical deploy topology is described in ARCHITECTURE.md §11, but the
# Dockerfile and compose configuration are not published.
Dockerfile
Dockerfile.*
docker-compose.yml
docker-compose.*.yml
compose.yml
compose.*.yml

# Build-time files generated by deploy workflow
BUILD_VERSION

# Operational / internal documentation deliberately not published.
# DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md describes the private production deploy topology;
# blog posts live at emberline.ch/blog, not in the repo;
# phase5-updated.md and privacy-comparison.md are internal working docs;
# the infrastructure SVG is a private deploy diagram.
DEPLOYMENT_GUIDE.md
blog-post.md
blog-post-encryption-deep-dive.md
phase5-updated.md
privacy-comparison.md
emberline-infrastructure.svg
*.docx

# Private keys — these should never be in the project directory.
# Belt-and-suspenders: even if a key file somehow lands here, git ignores it.
*.ppk
*.pem
*.key
id_rsa
id_rsa.*
id_ed25519
id_ed25519.*
known_hosts

# OS detritus
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
ehthumbs.db

# Editor / IDE local state
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
